The '''Benin Rebirth Party''' ({{lang-fr|Parti de la renaissance du Bénin}}) is an oppositional, more or less [[liberal parties|liberal party]] in [[Benin]]. The party is led by [[Nicéphore Soglo]], who was [[President of Benin]] from 1991 to 1996 and later Mayor of [[Cotonou]].

Soglo was the RB candidate in the [[Beninese presidential election, 2001|March 2001 presidential election]], taking second place with 27.1% of the popular vote in the first round, but he boycotted the second round. In the [[Beninese parliamentary election, 2003|parliamentary election]] held on 30 March 2003, the party won 15 out of 83 seats.

In early August 2005, the RB chose Soglo's son [[Lehady Soglo]] as its candidate for the [[Beninese presidential election, 2006|March 2006 presidential election]].<ref>"Benin: Ex-leader's son to run for presidency in 2006", Radio France Internationale, August 7, 2005.</ref> The elder Soglo could not run because of the constitutional age limit of 70 years for candidates. In the election, Lehady Soglo obtained 7.92% of the vote and placed fourth. 

In the [[Beninese parliamentary election, 2007|March 2007 parliamentary election]], the RB participated in the [[Alliance for a Dynamic Democracy]],<ref>Alain C. Assogba, [http://www.benininfo.com/060403.htm "Conclave à Cotonou hier : L’Add passe à l’offensive (Elle veut constituer sa propre majorité)"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070929011745/http://www.benininfo.com/060403.htm |date=2007-09-29 }}, ''La Nouvelle Tribune'', April 6, 2007.</ref> which won a total of 20 seats.<ref>[http://apanews.net/apa.php?page=show_article_eng&id_article=25205 "Coalition supported by President Boni tops Benin’s legislative polls"]{{dead link|date=July 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}, African Press Agency, April 8, 2007.</ref>

