{{Infobox Union |name= CIG |country= [[Spain (Spain)|Spain]] |affiliation= [[World Federation of Trade Unions|WFTU]] |members= more than 80,000 |full_name= Galician Unions Confederacy |native_name= Confederación Intersindical Galega |image=[[File:Bandeira-cig.png|200px]] |caption=Logo |founded= 1993 |Ideology= [[Galician nationalism]], [[Socialism]] [[Anticapitalism]] |current= |head= |dissolved_date= |dissolved_state= |merged_into= |office= [[Santiago de Compostela]], Galicia |people= [[Paulo Carril]], general secretary |website= [http://www.galizacig.gal/ galizacig.gal] |footnotes= }} <!-- Include all unused fields for future use. See [[template talk:Infobox Union]] for usage. -->
The '''Galician Unions Confederacy''' ({{lang-gl|italic=yes|Confederación Intersindical Galega, CIG}}) is a trade union in that was created after the merge of two previous unions: the [[Intersindical Nacional dos Traballadores Galegos|INTG]] and the [[Confederación Xeral de Traballadores Galegos-Intersindical Nacional|CXTG]]. It has a [[Galician nationalism|Galician nationalist]] and [[socialist]] ideology and generally defends a combative labour model, as opposed to the perceived mild tactics of the other two main unions in Galicia, [[CCOO]] and the [[Unión General de Trabajadores|UGT]]. The union has organized 6 general strikes in Galicia since its creation.<ref>http://folgaxeral.info/?page_id=19</ref>
Currently the CIG has 4,480 labour delegates (28.28% of the total)<ref>[https://www.sermosgaliza.gal/articulo/traballo/cig-xa-primeira-forza-sindical-galiza/20180628115711070152.html A CIG xa é a primeira forza sindical en Galiza]. Sermos Galiza, 29/06/2018.</ref> and more than 80,000 members, being the largest union in [[Galicia (Spain)|Galicia]] both in membership and delegates.
