{{unreferenced|date=April 2016}} {{Infobox song contest entry | song = {{flagicon|Turkey}} "Dinle" | image = | caption = | year = 1997 | country = Turkey | artist = [[Şebnem Paker]] | with = [[Grup Etnic]] | genre = | language = Turkish | languages = | composer = [[Levent Çoker]] | lyricist = Mehtap Alnıtemiz | conductor = [[Levent Çoker]] | place = 3rd | points = 121 | lyrics = [http://www.diggiloo.net/?1997tr from Diggiloo Thrush] | prev = Beşinci Mevsim | prev_link = Beşinci Mevsim | next = Unutamazsın | next_link = Unutamazsın }} '''"Dinle"''' ("Listen") was the [[Turkey|Turkish]] entrant to the [[Eurovision Song Contest 1997]] in [[Dublin]], [[Ireland]]. It was composed by [[Levent Çoker]] and Mehtap Alnıtemiz, and was performed by [[Şebnem Paker]] in [[Turkish language|Turkish]]. This was the second time that Paker had competed at Eurovision, having represented Turkey also at the [[Eurovision Song Contest 1996|1996 contest]] with "[[Beşinci Mevsim]]".
On the night it was performed second, following [[Cyprus]]'s [[Hara & Andreas Konstantinou]] singing "[[Mana Mu|Mana Mou]]" and preceding [[Norway]]'s [[Tor Endresen]] with "[[San Francisco (Tor Endresen song)|San Francisco]]". At the close of the voting it had received 121 points, placing third in a field of 25. This was Turkey's best position in the contest until their win in 2003, and is still the best position of a Turkish language entry at Eurovision as of 2017.
It was succeeded as Turkish representative at the [[Eurovision Song Contest 1998|1998 contest]] with Tüzmen and "[[Unutamazsın]]".
