'''''Inhlawulo''''' {{IPA-zu|int͡ɬawuːlo|}}, in [[Swaziland|Swazi]]/[[Zulu people|Zulu]] law, is a [[Fine (penalty)|fine]] or [[damages]] paid<ref>van R Whelpton, FP, Indigenous Swazi Law of Court Procedure: A Restatement, 2. ''2005 J. S. Afr. L.'' p. 348 (2005)</ref>

In [[Zulu people|Zulu]] culture, ''inhlawulo'' refers to damages paid to the family of a woman who became pregnant [[out of wedlock]] by the father of the future child.<ref>Wendy Annecke: ''The Unmarried Fathers' Fight''. Agenda, No. 7 (1990), pp. 62-65</ref>

