{{Infobox street | name = Kavaja Street | image = Streets in Tirana 010.jpg | image_size = 230px | image_alt = | caption = View of the Kavajë Street | image_dot_map = | dot_x = | dot_y = | quarter = | coordinates = | terminus_a = [[Skanderbeg Square]] | terminus_b = 21 Dhjetori | length = | width = | completion_date = | inauguration_label = | inauguration_date = }} '''Kavajë Street''' ({{lang-sq|Rruga e Kavajës}}) is a major street of [[Tirana]], [[Albania]]. It is the most important street of western Tirana and runs west from the central [[Skanderbeg Square]] for several kilometres and continues further west to the Adriatic Sea. It is known for its prime real estate and some of the most expensive residential apartments in Tirana. The [[Universal Hospital Tirana]] is located along this street.<ref>Jeroen van Marle, Alwyn Thomson, ''Tirana In Your Pocket'', p.20</ref> It intersects with [[Bajram Curri Boulevard]].
