{{Politics of San Marino}}

The '''RETE Movement''' ({{lang-it|Rinnovamento, Equità, Transparenza, Ecosostenibilità Movimento Civico}}, lit. ''Renewal, Equity, Transparency and Eco-sustainability Civic Movement'') is a political party in [[San Marino]].

==History==
The party was formed by several activist groups involved in the environmental, civic rights and arts.<ref name=TL>Tom Lansford (2015) ''Political Handbook of the World 2015'', CQ Press</ref> It contested the [[Sammarinese general election, 2012|2012 general elections]], receiving 6.3% of the vote and winning four seats.<ref name=TL/>

